    • Method Detail

      • login

        public static Employee login(String username,
                             String password)
                      throws CarportException
        Finds an employee in the database. If the Employee exists in the employees table, it will be returned, so an entity can be created and returned.
        Parameters:
        username - String type not null.
        password - String type not null.
        Returns:
        An Employee Object if the given Employee exists in the database.
        Throws:
        CarportException - If the Employee does not exist in the database.

      • registerEmp

        public static void registerEmp(String username,
                               String password,
                               String role)
                        throws CarportException
        Inserts a new employee to the database. With the given parameters a new employee will be created in the employees table, in the database.
        Parameters:
        username - String type not null.
        password - String type not null.
        role - String type not null.
        Throws:
        CarportException - If something goes wrong, trying to insert into the database, an exception will be thrown to be displayed on registeremployee.jsp.

      • deleteEmployee

        public static void deleteEmployee(int userID)
                           throws CarportException
        An employee will get deleted from the database. With the given parameter, the employee with the unique userID gets removed from the employees table, in the database.
        Parameters:
        userID - int type always 1 or higher, to match one of the userID's in the database.
        Throws:
        CarportException - If something fails trying to delete the given employee from the database, an exception will be thrown and displayed on employee.jsp.

      • getAllEmployees

        public static List<Employee> getAllEmployees()
                                      throws CarportException
        Creates a list of all employees in the database. For every row in the database, a new Employee entity will be created and added to a list.
        Returns:
        a List of all Employees in the database.
        Throws:
        CarportException - if something goes wrong trying to fetch all of the employees.

      • loginCustomer

        public static Customer loginCustomer(String email,
                                     String password)
                              throws CarportException
        Finds a customer from the database. With the given parameters a customer might be found from the customers table, to login on the site. Every time a customer succesfully logs in or fail to do so, it will be logged.
        Parameters:
        email - type string, not null.
        password - type string, not null.
        Returns:
        a Customer entity object, to be used when logged in.
        Throws:
        CarportException - if no user exists, with the given parameters or if something goes wrong trying to fetch one.

      • getCustomer

        public static Customer getCustomer(int customerID)
                            throws CarportException
        Finds a customer with the given unique customerID. If the customer is in the customers table, it will be used, to display contact info on ordermanagement.jsp, using the include file Userinfo.jspf.
        Parameters:
        customerID - int type always 1 or higher, to match one of the existing customers in the database.
        Returns:
        a Customer entity object.
        Throws:
        CarportException - if the customer cannot be found in the database or if something goes wrong trying to fetch it.

      • registerCustomer

        public static void registerCustomer(Customer customer)
                             throws CarportException
        A customer will be inserted into the database. With the given parameter, a new customer will be inserted into the customers table.
        Parameters:
        customer - Customer entity type, which gets created in RegisterCustomer.java
        Throws:
        CarportException - if something goes wrong trying to insert the customer to the customers table.
